{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":960,"text":"This story begins in 1985,"},{"time":3960,"text":"when at age 22,"},{"time":5960,"text":"I became the World Chess Champion"},{"time":8360,"text":"after beating Anatoly Karpov."},{"time":12480,"text":"Earlier that year,"},{"time":13760,"text":"I played what is called\nsimultaneous exhibition"},{"time":17400,"text":"against 32 of the world's\nbest chess-playing machines"},{"time":21720,"text":"in Hamburg, Germany."},{"time":24160,"text":"I won all the games,"},{"time":26560,"text":"and then it was not considered\nmuch of a surprise"},{"time":29760,"text":"that I could beat 32 computers\nat the same time."},{"time":34480,"text":"To me, that was the golden age."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37080,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":39200,"text":"Machines were weak,"},{"time":41680,"text":"and my hair was strong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43040,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":46720,"text":"Just 12 years later,"},{"time":48800,"text":"I was fighting for my life\nagainst just one computer"},{"time":53440,"text":"in a match"},{"time":55360,"text":"called by the cover of \"Newsweek\""},{"time":57440,"text":"\"The Brain's Last Stand.\""},{"time":59240,"text":"No pressure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60480,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":63040,"text":"From mythology to science fiction,"},{"time":65640,"text":"human versus machine"},{"time":68400,"text":"has been often portrayed\nas a matter of life and death."},{"time":71960,"text":"John Henry,"},{"time":73560,"text":"called the steel-driving man"},{"time":75280,"text":"in the 19th century\nAfrican American folk legend,"},{"time":79080,"text":"was pitted in a race"},{"time":80480,"text":"against a steam-powered hammer"},{"time":83240,"text":"bashing a tunnel through mountain rock."},{"time":86800,"text":"John Henry's legend\nis a part of a long historical narrative"},{"time":91680,"text":"pitting humanity versus technology."},{"time":96200,"text":"And this competitive rhetoric\nis standard now."},{"time":99560,"text":"We are in a race against the machines,"},{"time":102360,"text":"in a fight or even in a war."},{"time":105880,"text":"Jobs are being killed off."},{"time":107520,"text":"People are being replaced\nas if they had vanished from the Earth."},{"time":112240,"text":"It's enough to think that the movies\nlike \"The Terminator\" or \"The Matrix\""},{"time":115760,"text":"are nonfiction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119640,"text":"There are very few instances of an arena"},{"time":125360,"text":"where the human body and mind\ncan compete on equal terms"},{"time":129639,"text":"with a computer or a robot."},{"time":132280,"text":"Actually, I wish there were a few more."},{"time":135760,"text":"Instead,"},{"time":137840,"text":"it was my blessing and my curse"},{"time":142520,"text":"to literally become the proverbial man"},{"time":145240,"text":"in the man versus machine competition"},{"time":148360,"text":"that everybody is still talking about."},{"time":153120,"text":"In the most famous human-machine\ncompetition since John Henry,"},{"time":158160,"text":"I played two matches"},{"time":160760,"text":"against the IBM supercomputer, Deep Blue."},{"time":167040,"text":"Nobody remembers\nthat I won the first match --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":169240,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":171600,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":175920,"text":"In Philadelphia, before losing the rematch\nthe following year in New York."},{"time":180920,"text":"But I guess that's fair."},{"time":184320,"text":"There is no day in history,\nspecial calendar entry"},{"time":189440,"text":"for all the people\nwho failed to climb Mt. Everest"},{"time":192960,"text":"before Sir Edmund Hillary\nand Tenzing Norgay"},{"time":195720,"text":"made it to the top."},{"time":197960,"text":"And in 1997, I was still\nthe world champion"},{"time":204520,"text":"when chess computers finally came of age."},{"time":209520,"text":"I was Mt. Everest,"},{"time":211520,"text":"and Deep Blue reached the summit."},{"time":214600,"text":"I should say of course,\nnot that Deep Blue did it,"},{"time":218680,"text":"but its human creators --"},{"time":220840,"text":"Anantharaman, Campbell, Hoane, Hsu."},{"time":224200,"text":"Hats off to them."},{"time":226840,"text":"As always, machine's triumph\nwas a human triumph,"},{"time":231280,"text":"something we tend to forget when humans\nare surpassed by our own creations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238360,"text":"Deep Blue was victorious,"},{"time":241400,"text":"but was it intelligent?"},{"time":243360,"text":"No, no it wasn't,"},{"time":246200,"text":"at least not in the way Alan Turing\nand other founders of computer science"},{"time":251280,"text":"had hoped."},{"time":253240,"text":"It turned out that chess\ncould be crunched by brute force,"},{"time":258040,"text":"once hardware got fast enough"},{"time":262320,"text":"and algorithms got smart enough."},{"time":266760,"text":"Although by the definition of the output,"},{"time":270480,"text":"grandmaster-level chess,"},{"time":273720,"text":"Deep Blue was intelligent."},{"time":277320,"text":"But even at the incredible speed,"},{"time":280560,"text":"200 million positions per second,"},{"time":285360,"text":"Deep Blue's method"},{"time":287360,"text":"provided little of the dreamed-of insight\ninto the mysteries of human intelligence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296960,"text":"Soon,"},{"time":298800,"text":"machines will be taxi drivers"},{"time":301400,"text":"and doctors and professors,"},{"time":303840,"text":"but will they be \"intelligent?\""},{"time":307840,"text":"I would rather leave these definitions"},{"time":310360,"text":"to the philosophers and to the dictionary."},{"time":315440,"text":"What really matters is how we humans"},{"time":320320,"text":"feel about living and working\nwith these machines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326160,"text":"When I first met Deep Blue\nin 1996 in February,"},{"time":331440,"text":"I had been the world champion\nfor more than 10 years,"},{"time":336080,"text":"and I had played 182\nworld championship games"},{"time":340120,"text":"and hundreds of games against\nother top players in other competitions."},{"time":345240,"text":"I knew what to expect from my opponents"},{"time":350320,"text":"and what to expect from myself."},{"time":352680,"text":"I was used to measure their moves"},{"time":357880,"text":"and to gauge their emotional state"},{"time":361520,"text":"by watching their body language\nand looking into their eyes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365880,"text":"And then I sat across\nthe chessboard from Deep Blue."},{"time":372960,"text":"I immediately sensed something new,"},{"time":375840,"text":"something unsettling."},{"time":379440,"text":"You might experience a similar feeling"},{"time":383320,"text":"the first time you ride\nin a driverless car"},{"time":385880,"text":"or the first time your new computer\nmanager issues an order at work."},{"time":393800,"text":"But when I sat at that first game,"},{"time":398080,"text":"I couldn't be sure"},{"time":400240,"text":"what is this thing capable of."},{"time":404920,"text":"Technology can advance in leaps,\nand IBM had invested heavily."},{"time":408680,"text":"I lost that game."},{"time":412320,"text":"And I couldn't help wondering,"},{"time":414120,"text":"might it be invincible?"},{"time":416600,"text":"Was my beloved game of chess over?"},{"time":420800,"text":"These were human doubts, human fears,"},{"time":424960,"text":"and the only thing I knew for sure"},{"time":427400,"text":"was that my opponent Deep Blue\nhad no such worries at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":430320,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":433920,"text":"I fought back"},{"time":436400,"text":"after this devastating blow"},{"time":439000,"text":"to win the first match,"},{"time":440960,"text":"but the writing was on the wall."},{"time":444400,"text":"I eventually lost to the machine"},{"time":446560,"text":"but I didn't suffer the fate of John Henry"},{"time":449640,"text":"who won but died\nwith his hammer in his hand."},{"time":452718,"text":"[John Henry Died with a Hammer in His Hand\nPalmer C. Hayden]"},{"time":455580,"text":"[The Museum of African\nAmerican Art, Los Angeles]"},{"time":457910,"text":"It turned out that the world of chess"},{"time":460280,"text":"still wanted to have\na human chess champion."},{"time":464920,"text":"And even today,"},{"time":468080,"text":"when a free chess app\non the latest mobile phone"},{"time":471560,"text":"is stronger than Deep Blue,"},{"time":473600,"text":"people are still playing chess,"},{"time":476680,"text":"even more than ever before."},{"time":479800,"text":"Doomsayers predicted\nthat nobody would touch the game"},{"time":483040,"text":"that could be conquered by the machine,"},{"time":485320,"text":"and they were wrong, proven wrong,"},{"time":487560,"text":"but doomsaying has always been\na popular pastime"},{"time":491040,"text":"when it comes to technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494360,"text":"What I learned from my own experience"},{"time":497120,"text":"is that we must face our fears"},{"time":501800,"text":"if we want to get the most\nout of our technology,"},{"time":506360,"text":"and we must conquer those fears"},{"time":508760,"text":"if we want to get the best\nout of our humanity."},{"time":516120,"text":"While licking my wounds,"},{"time":517919,"text":"I got a lot of inspiration"},{"time":521080,"text":"from my battles against Deep Blue."},{"time":523799,"text":"As the old Russian saying goes,\nif you can't beat them, join them."},{"time":528880,"text":"Then I thought,"},{"time":530280,"text":"what if I could play with a computer --"},{"time":532640,"text":"together with a computer at my side,\ncombining our strengths,"},{"time":537160,"text":"human intuition\nplus machine's calculation,"},{"time":540960,"text":"human strategy, machine tactics,"},{"time":543680,"text":"human experience, machine's memory."},{"time":546120,"text":"Could it be the perfect game ever played?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":550000,"text":"My idea came to life"},{"time":552920,"text":"in 1998 under the name of Advanced Chess"},{"time":556320,"text":"when I played this human-plus-machine\ncompetition against another elite player."},{"time":563280,"text":"But in this first experiment,"},{"time":565200,"text":"we both failed to combine\nhuman and machine skills effectively."},{"time":574920,"text":"Advanced Chess found\nits home on the internet,"},{"time":578160,"text":"and in 2005, a so-called\nfreestyle chess tournament"},{"time":583040,"text":"produced a revelation."},{"time":587240,"text":"A team of grandmasters\nand top machines participated,"},{"time":590800,"text":"but the winners were not grandmasters,"},{"time":593560,"text":"not a supercomputer."},{"time":595680,"text":"The winners were a pair\nof amateur American chess players"},{"time":600040,"text":"operating three ordinary PCs\nat the same time."},{"time":605560,"text":"Their skill of coaching their machines"},{"time":608600,"text":"effectively counteracted\nthe superior chess knowledge"},{"time":614400,"text":"of their grandmaster opponents"},{"time":616000,"text":"and much greater\ncomputational power of others."},{"time":621600,"text":"And I reached this formulation."},{"time":624560,"text":"A weak human player plus a machine"},{"time":627960,"text":"plus a better process is superior"},{"time":631240,"text":"to a very powerful machine alone,"},{"time":633680,"text":"but more remarkably,\nis superior to a strong human player"},{"time":637600,"text":"plus machine"},{"time":641120,"text":"and an inferior process."},{"time":646360,"text":"This convinced me that we would need"},{"time":650000,"text":"better interfaces\nto help us coach our machines"},{"time":654520,"text":"towards more useful intelligence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":658320,"text":"Human plus machine isn't the future,"},{"time":661640,"text":"it's the present."},{"time":662880,"text":"Everybody that's used online translation"},{"time":667040,"text":"to get the gist of a news article\nfrom a foreign newspaper,"},{"time":671360,"text":"knowing its far from perfect."},{"time":673680,"text":"Then we use our human experience"},{"time":675800,"text":"to make sense out of that,"},{"time":677920,"text":"and then the machine\nlearns from our corrections."},{"time":680720,"text":"This model is spreading and investing\nin medical diagnosis, security analysis."},{"time":686440,"text":"The machine crunches data,"},{"time":689320,"text":"calculates probabilities,"},{"time":691080,"text":"gets 80 percent of the way, 90 percent,"},{"time":694760,"text":"making it easier for analysis"},{"time":699160,"text":"and decision-making of the human party."},{"time":702280,"text":"But you are not going to send your kids"},{"time":708000,"text":"to school in a self-driving car\nwith 90 percent accuracy,"},{"time":712600,"text":"even with 99 percent."},{"time":715560,"text":"So we need a leap forward"},{"time":718440,"text":"to add a few more crucial decimal places."}]},{"cues":[{"time":727160,"text":"Twenty years after\nmy match with Deep Blue,"},{"time":732200,"text":"second match,"},{"time":733840,"text":"this sensational\n\"The Brain's Last Stand\" headline"},{"time":740160,"text":"has become commonplace"},{"time":741760,"text":"as intelligent machines"},{"time":744320,"text":"move"},{"time":746560,"text":"in every sector, seemingly every day."},{"time":750160,"text":"But unlike in the past,"},{"time":753280,"text":"when machines replaced"},{"time":756480,"text":"farm animals, manual labor,"},{"time":758880,"text":"now they are coming\nafter people with college degrees"},{"time":761400,"text":"and political influence."},{"time":764120,"text":"And as someone\nwho fought machines and lost,"},{"time":766240,"text":"I am here to tell you\nthis is excellent, excellent news."},{"time":771000,"text":"Eventually, every profession"},{"time":773240,"text":"will have to feel these pressures"},{"time":775360,"text":"or else it will mean humanity\nhas ceased to make progress."},{"time":782760,"text":"We don't"},{"time":785440,"text":"get to choose"},{"time":788480,"text":"when and where\ntechnological progress stops."},{"time":793160,"text":"We cannot"},{"time":795960,"text":"slow down."},{"time":797480,"text":"In fact,"},{"time":799320,"text":"we have to speed up."},{"time":804600,"text":"Our technology excels at removing"},{"time":809200,"text":"difficulties and uncertainties\nfrom our lives,"},{"time":815000,"text":"and so we must seek out"},{"time":817840,"text":"ever more difficult,"},{"time":819720,"text":"ever more uncertain challenges."},{"time":828200,"text":"Machines have"},{"time":831880,"text":"calculations."},{"time":833720,"text":"We have understanding."},{"time":835320,"text":"Machines have instructions."},{"time":838840,"text":"We have purpose."},{"time":840720,"text":"Machines have"},{"time":845080,"text":"objectivity."},{"time":846320,"text":"We have passion."},{"time":848600,"text":"We should not worry\nabout what our machines can do today."},{"time":854600,"text":"Instead, we should worry\nabout what they still cannot do today,"},{"time":859200,"text":"because we will need the help\nof the new, intelligent machines"},{"time":864720,"text":"to turn our grandest dreams into reality."},{"time":870000,"text":"And if we fail,"},{"time":872240,"text":"if we fail, it's not because our machines\nare too intelligent,"},{"time":876920,"text":"or not intelligent enough."},{"time":879200,"text":"If we fail, it's because\nwe grew complacent"},{"time":883680,"text":"and limited our ambitions."},{"time":886520,"text":"Our humanity is not defined by any skill,"},{"time":891280,"text":"like swinging a hammer\nor even playing chess."}]},{"cues":[{"time":894560,"text":"There's one thing only a human can do."},{"time":897600,"text":"That's dream."},{"time":900120,"text":"So let us dream big."}]},{"cues":[{"time":902680,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":903920,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}